This Rest API was created using Golang and mongodb. It features functions like sign up login and getting user details from database.
This api has used authentication mechanism, middle ware and different clean code principles.
In order to use this Api:
1. clone the repo : $ git clone https://github.com/vatsal278/Go-Api-with-Authentication-Mechanism.git
2. build the docker file : $ docker build .
3. Pull official mongodb image from docker hub : $ docker pull mongo
4. Create a new isolated docker network : $ docker network create -d bridge api_net
5. Start a mongo server instance : $ docker run --network api_net --name mongo-container-name -d mongo
6. run the container using command : $ docker run --network api_net --publish 9092(any available port):8080 image_name(use your own image name)

